<TITLE> Faridpur crash death toll 20 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Faridpur, Dec 7 (bdnews24.com)--Officials on Monday revised the death toll in Sunday's bus accident on the Dhaka-Barisal highway at Bhanga to 20. The administration on Sunday night said the number was 21. Bhanga Upazila Nirbahi Officer Mohammad Shafiqul Islam said the actual number of dead is 20 and the bodies have been returned to the relatives. Shipping minister Shahjahan Khan visited the spot early on Monday and ordered the officials to form a committee to investigate the incident. He later went to the Faridpur Medical College Hospital (FMCH) and Bhanga Upazila Health Complex to see the injured. Officials of the district administration and the police accompanied him. Deputy commissioner Helaluddin Ahmed told reporters on Monday the reason behind the accident will be revealed once the enquiry committee completes its job. The minister pledged to establish a trauma centre in Bhanga, he added. Islam, the UNO, said five injured persons were taking treatment at Bhanga Upazila Health Complex. Local administration gave them Tk 1,000 each. The accident also left 40 people injured, 15 of whom are under treatment in FMCH. Seventeen of them were sent to different hospitals in Dhaka, superintendent of FMCH Dipti Rani Saha told bdnews24.com. bdnews24.com
